API Test Flow

Login (auth) --> delete cart
 --> add to cart (productId, quantity, size, color, fulfilment)
  --> place order (paymentMethod, address, shipping, coupon)
  --> get order by id (confirm created order details)
  --> allocate order (status becomes ALLOCATED)
  --> ship order (status becomes SHIPPED)

Description:
This API testing covers full order flow from login to shipping.
It also includes negative test cases like missing token, invalid token,
expired token and no permission (403)   .
Then main flow starts where I login and get token, clear cart,
add items, place order, and verify response using status code and schema.
After that I fetch same order using GET and then move order status from
CREATED → ALLOCATED → SHIPPED. Each step checks response data and status code.

DB Test Flow

Description:
In DB testing, I created order using API and then connect to database using JDBC.
I fetch same order using orderId and check if data is saved properly.
Then I verify status is CREATED and total value in DB matches API response.

create order through API -->
get orderId from response -->
fetch same order from database using JDBC -->
verify record exists --> check status is CREATED -->
compare total from API response and database value (both must match)